args: So you want me to put on a display\nin your town? Certainly. I'll be along\non the day of the festival.
Thanks a million! I can't wait!
Your fireworks are supposed to be\nsuuuuuper crazy beautiful!
Well, I don't know if I'd go THAT far.
Ha ha! I'm just trying to tell you how\nexcited we all are. See ya!
Someone from another town who wants\nme to put on a pyroblossom display.
People are coming to you now?\nThat's amazing!
He said he heard about me through\nsomeone else. It's all rather remarkable.
It's humbling to know word is spreading,\nbut it also makes me happy.
I say! I hear there is some manner of\npyroblossom artisan in this castle?
Sounds like you just got another visitor.
Then I shall get straight to the point.
A festival will soon be held in the city\nwhere I live, and I want one of your\ndisplays to close the occasion.
I did not expect you to agree so readily.\nWe've not even discussed payment!
You would hand over something\nso valuable for free?!
What utter madness! Still, if this is how\nyou wish to do business, I'll not argue.
And now, I must take my leave of you.\nGood day.
Well, I find myself wondering if that man\ntruly wants to see my work.
Usually people tell me that they want\nto see them because they're beautiful,\nbut that man used the word ＂valuable.＂
Hmm. I suppose he didn't seem excited in\nthe same way other people usually are.
Oh, but I'm not going to give less than\nmy best because of that, of course.
I'd be a failure as an artisan if I gave\nanything less than 100 percent to a job!
Well, I must get ready. Excuse me.
I have to respect the way Su Fang thinks.
Still, calling his pyroblossoms ＂valuable＂\nWAS a little bit odd...
Time passed, and the day came for Su Fang and\nthe prince to pay a visit to the noble.
Ah, Su Fang! How good to see you again.
The festival will be held a short distance\nfrom here. Might you accompany me?
Oh, that won't be necessary; I've readied\nthe finest seats in all the city for you\nto watch the show!
Well, ain't that sweet of ya!\nC'mon, {player_name}.
We're being led somewhere else? Hmm...
Are we nearly there? We seem to be\ngetting further and further from the\ncenter of the city.
Actually, I think we have just arrived.\nYoo hoo! Oh, boys! Come on out!
Don't worry 'bout that none, little man!\nYou just drop them fancy fireworks 'ere.
I'm sorry, but I cannot do that.\nThese mean everything to me.
Surely not more than your life?
You... This was your goal all along!
Indeed! Oh, but I have heard SUCH tales\nabout your magnificent creations.
To think you would take such a powerful\nweapon and use it as a mere amusement!\nAh ha! Aha ha ha! What madness!
I have FAR better plans in store...
Like taking over the city and laying waste\nto all who try to stop me! Aaaaa ha ha ha!
'Ow's that, little man? Couldn't hear ya!
How dare you even THINK of using my\npyroblossoms for something so shameful?!
And here I was hoping we could reach a\npeaceful agreement. It's SUCH a shame.\n...Ah, well. Teach him a lesson, boys!
N-no! You're not supposed to be here!
Clearly I was right to be suspicious of you.
That's why I followed you here.
Argh! This is SUCH a silly way for my\nbeautiful plan to fail! Run awaaaay!
Are you okay, Su Fang? Are you hurt?
I'm fine, but that lout escaped!
I don't care—I just need to know you're\nall right. I've never seen you so angry!
Ah, yes. That. I guess that man just\nraised something up in me.
He was about to breach one of the key\nrules of a pyroblossom artisan, you see.
Yes. Before we learn how to create and\nlight pyroblossoms, we learn the state of\nmind required to handle them.
They can be exceedingly dangerous,\nand so a true artisan must clear the\nmind and heart of all possible distraction.
I wish there were more people\nin the world like you, Su Fang.
Oh, I'm nothing special! I've done things\nI'm not very proud of, after all.
Still, this taught me a valuable lesson:\nThere are people out there who would\nuse my craft for great evil.
I must increase my vigilance and ensure\nthey are used only to spread joy—not fear.
It seems my dream is further away\nthan I first supposed.
